            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>Before Allocating Budget: Complete These 4 Preparations</h2>
<p>Budget allocation is not the first step—preparation determines whether your allocation is reasonable.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] <strong>Clarify current stage goals</strong>: Is it cold-start user acquisition, product scaling, or seasonal promotion? Different stages require different budget priorities.</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Review existing data</strong>: What are your CPA, CPM, and ROAS across channels in the past 30 days? Which products/audiences perform consistently?</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Confirm total budget</strong>: What is the upper limit of monthly or weekly ad spend? Are there financial checkpoints to consider?</li>
<li>[ ] <strong>Identify priority products</strong>: With limited budget, which 1-2 products get the focus? Concentrating resources on a bestseller is more controllable than scattered投放.</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Warning</strong>: If you have less than 30 days of data, run a small budget (~$50-100/day per channel) for 2 weeks before formal allocation. Avoid over-spending during the testing phase.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2>Channel Budget Allocation: Reference Ratios and Adjustment Logic</h2>
<p>Different channels have varying traffic costs and conversion paths. Use this framework for initial distribution, then adjust dynamically based on performance.</p>
<h3>1. Search Ads (Google Ads, Bing) — Best for Users with Clear Purchase Intent</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Recommended ratio: 30%-40%</strong></li>
<li><strong>Best for</strong>: Brand terms, competitor terms, product keywords</li>
<li><strong>Checklist</strong>:</li>
<li>[ ] Keyword Quality Score ≥ 7</li>
<li>[ ] Search ad CTR ≥ 3%</li>
<li>[ ] Shopping ad product Feed is complete and updated</li>
</ul>
<h3>2. Social Ads (Meta, Google Pmax Integration) — Great for Retargeting Interest Groups</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Recommended ratio: 35%-45%</strong></li>
<li><strong>Best for</strong>: Retargeting users, Lookalike expansion, A/B testing creatives</li>
<li><strong>Checklist</strong>:</li>
<li>[ ] Retargeting audience includes add-to-cart but no-purchase users</li>
<li>[ ] Budget for new vs. returning customers tracked separately</li>
<li>[ ] Creative iteration frequency: at least one refresh every 2 weeks</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. TikTok Video Ads — Ideal for Impulse-Buy Products</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Recommended ratio: 15%-25%</strong></li>
<li><strong>Best for</strong>: Visually striking products, younger demographic audiences</li>
<li><strong>Checklist</strong>:</li>
<li>[ ] First 3 seconds retention rate ≥ 50%</li>
<li>[ ] CTR ≥ 1.5% (TikTok CPM is low but the conversion funnel is wider)</li>
<li>[ ] TikTok Pixel installed for tracking in-site behavior</li>
</ul>
<h3>4. Backup/Exploration Channels — Flexible Pool</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Recommended ratio: 5%-10%</strong></li>
<li>Used for testing new channels (Snapchat, Pinterest) or new markets</li>
<li><strong>Checklist</strong>:</li>
<li>[ ] Clear test KPI set (e.g., CPA ≤ $15)</li>
<li>[ ] Test period does not exceed 3 weeks; pause if KPIs not met</li>
</ul>
<h2>Weekly Budget Execution Checklist</h2>
<p>Post-allocation, monitoring during execution is equally important. Use this checklist for weekly reviews:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Actual spend vs. planned spend: Is the deviation more than ±15%?</li>
<li>[ ] Core metrics on track: ROAS ≥ target? CPA ≤ product price × 30%?</li>
<li>[ ] Any anomalies: Sudden spend increase but lower conversions may signal creative fatigue or competitor bidding.</li>
<li>[ ] Sufficient balance: Alert 2 days in advance to avoid account suspension affecting data stability.</li>
<li>[ ] Any budget adjustments needed next week: Allocate more to high-performing channels based on this week's data.</li>
</ul>
<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Q: With limited budget, should I run multiple channels simultaneously or concentrate on one?</strong><br />
A: Start with 1-2 channels for 2-4 weeks until you find a stable CPA, then expand. Scattered budgets may keep each channel from exiting the "learning phase," making data consistently unreliable.</p>
<p><strong>Q: How to adjust budget during peak seasons?</strong><br />
A: Begin gradually increasing spend 2 weeks before major promotions. Total budget can increase 50%-100%, with focus on search ads (capturing active demand) and retargeting (converting hesitant users).</p>
<hr />
<p>Budget allocation is a dynamic process. The core principle is: "Decide based on data first, then scale after testing." Use this checklist to avoid detours and make every advertising dollar count.</p>
